President Biden spoke with President Xi Jinping of China regarding Russia's invasion of Ukraine. Biden outlined the United States' stance on the crisis and the actions taken to prevent and respond to the invasion. He warned of consequences if China supports Russia's attacks on Ukraine. Both leaders emphasized the importance of communication to manage the competition between their countries. Biden reiterated the US policy on Taiwan and opposition to any unilateral changes to the status quo. Their teams were tasked with following up on the conversation.